-- Chrysler says 2008 "looks very tough"
-- 
-- Mon Dec 3, 2007 4:14pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/12/03/us-chrysler-outlook-idUSN0356372020071203

 

 DETROIT  (Reuters) - Chrysler LLC's Vice President of U.S. Sales Darryl Jackson said on Monday that the automaker will adjust its North American production schedule weekly in 2008 as the year "looks very tough." 

 "Next year looks very tough, so we will be adjusting our schedules on a weekly basis," Jackson said on a conference call. The automaker also said it had 480,424 vehicles in its inventory at the end of November, 18,000 vehicles lower than year-ago, Jackson also said Chrysler's fleet sales in November were up while retail sales were "down a little." He declined to give exact numbers. (Reporting by  Poornima Gupta , editing by Leslie Gevirtz)